-- Norway's oil fund buys into Boston property for $122 mln
-- 
-- Mon Jul 28, 2014 10:42AM EDT
-- None



OSLO, July 28 (Reuters) - Norway's $890 billion sovereign wealth fund bought a 47.5 percent stake in a Boston office property for $122.3 million in a deal that valued the asset at $561.5 million dollars, it said on Monday.

The Fund bought the stake in the office building at One Beacon Street in a joint venture with MetLife <MET.N>, which owns the rest of the 1 million square-foot building and will perform the asset management of the property.